title: Captain Marvel Thoughts
body:
Firstly: rumors of my death have been greatly exaggerated… I am at least 65% alive, despite this summer’s efforts.

Now then, that that is out of the way, about the newest Marvel news:

I haven’t really made it a secret that I’m in love with Carol Danvers and less than thrilled with the casting decisions for Captain Marvel, but I’ve tried to remain cautiously optimistic, if only because I need the movie to do well and Marvel hasn’t let me down too painfully just yet.  There’s a lot of things I loved about the trailer - the badassery of her action sequences, especially going Binary at the end of the trailer, the sequences of young Carol, of her getting knocked down and repeatedly getting back up.  I did get choked up during the whole “See what makes HER / A HERO” because I’m easily played like that.  I still think she should be older, but I’ll shut up about it for a bit and give Brie a chance.  That being said… I don’t know how fond I am of the brainwashing idea, if only because part of the reason I love Carol so much is that she has such awesome powers but is still so human - so making her introduction at a point when she doesn’t remember Earth is a weird character arc, imho.  That being said, I get that they want her to be at the height of her powers to take on Thanos, and I suppose if they’ll give her the flashbacks and at least establish her as Carol Danvers, Air Force, Avenger by the end… I’ll let it go.

And then I saw the fucking silhouette of the cat on the poster and flipped out - if they don’t deliver with Chewie I’m gonna sue, fam.  Especially after that teaser.

And on that note, I’ve already decided I want a mid-credits and after-credits stinger.  The mid-credits of course will inevitably set up Infinity War 2 - my guess is it’ll be Carol somewhere off in space kicking all of the intergalactic ass, then getting her page and looking back across the cosmos towards Earth, knowing it’s time for the royal rumble.  But then I really want a second, after-credits scene.  And here’s my hope for Chewie - there’s no explanation, there’s nothing special about her, she’s just a grumpy looking tabby that Carol has carted around across the galaxy, a stray she picked up somewhere, that just confuses people that this ridiculously powerful super being is also a cat lady.  To a dumpy looking, unimpressive stray at that.  

So during the final sequence, after the credits have finished, we come back from the black screen to some nondescript alleyway on Earth, where some random shady guy is doing random shady things - nothing blatant, but enough that we know we can’t trust him.  And after a few seconds of watching him, suddenly there’s a music sting and he’s attacked by tentacles, turning to a Skrull as he’s pulled off-screen.  Cue a couple of random screams and crunch/slurp gross eating noises, as we’re left to wonder WTF alien attack we’re dealing with here - only for the camera to pan to Chewie, sitting on a fire escape and daintily licking her paw.  A second later the window opens and Carol calls out for her, before admonishing her for sneaking away and saying they have to go, scooping her up and disappearing off-screen again.

CAPTAIN MARVEL WILL RETURN WITH THE AVENGERS
